      "raw_text": "\n\n\n\"This ordinance. as counsel for\nthe defense says, is blanket-like\nprohibition, and 1t is unreasonable.\nThere is no doubt that the laws\ncarry for every municipality the\nright to regulate street speaking,\nbut 1t gives no municipality the\nright to abolish free speech. There\nis no question In mind but that this\nordinance Is invalid, andn | shall\ndeclare It such and dismiss this\ncase\"\n\n\nCourt Scene.\n\n\nAt these words. the municipal\ncourt room rang with wild, enthusi-\nastic cheering and elapplng of\nhands. and the Judge and Bailiff\nSmith shouted loudly and sternly\nseveral times before. order was re-\nstored. Judge Mann's explanation\nthat his decision concerning the\nnew ordinance would Immediately\nbring the old ordinance into effect\nngain was received with blank\nstares and profound silence. 1t was\naltogether unexpected."
    }
